<hr />
<h2>February 23, 2018:</h2>
<h1>Time-Lock Puzzles in Relation to Bitcoin</h1>
<h2>Grady Yu</h2>

<p>Time-lock puzzles enable a published message to be decoded only after
a set time period has elapsed. The original construction by
<a href="http://bitsavers.trailing-edge.com/pdf/mit/lcs/tr/MIT-LCS-TR-684.pdf">Rivest,
Shamir, and Wagner (1996)</a> relies upon "inherently sequential computation" and
standard RSA hardness. An alternative approach shown by
<a href="https://eprint.iacr.org/2015/478.pdf">Jager (2015)</a>
treats the Bitcoin network as a "computational reference clock" to avoid
the expensive decoding step.</p>

